<!--
  Closes the Layer 1 debt — canonical BoMs + 8-station routings
  for the 11 SB-* cabinets that the SB-BASE-1DR baseline didn't
  cover. Before this commit, Send-to-Production returned
  {error: 'no_bom_lines'} for any order whose only cabinet was
  not SB-BASE-1DR.

  Cycle-time methodology:

  Times scale from SB-BASE-1DR (12+8+6+25+10+8+5+4=78 min) by a
  complexity multiplier per cabinet. Per-station numbers are
  rounded so floor managers see clean integer minutes:

     Cabinet           Mult  Total min  Notes
     SB-WALL-1DR       0.75      60     small, single door
     SB-WALL-2DR       0.85      66     small, two doors
     SB-BASE-2DR       1.15      91     larger, two doors
     SB-DRAWER         —         98     no Hang Door step
     SB-SINK-BASE      1.15      91     sink cutout
     SB-TALL-PANTRY    1.50     118     large carcass
     SB-TALL-OVEN      1.50     118     appliance cutout
     SB-CORNER         1.60     125     bi-fold + corner geometry
     SB-VANITY         1.10      87     shallower depth than base
     SB-ACCESSORY      —          9     Cut/Edge/QC/Pack only
                                         (end panels, fillers,
                                          cornice — no carcass/door/HW)
     SB-WORKTOP        —         33     Cut/Edge/QC/Pack only
                                         (flat slab — no carcass)

  These are Phase-1 baselines. The PM tunes per actual run data
  once the work-order start/stop scanning lands in Layer 3.

  BoM sequence=0 on every record so the canonical BoM wins the
  tie-break against any cruft BoMs hanging around from earlier
  demo runs (same pattern as bom_base_1dr in routing_base_1dr.xml).
-->
